Are you inspired by the power of digital? Are you prepared to be challenged and empowered? We want you to be a part of our digital transformation journey!

What’s On Offer?
We are seeking a Customer Solution Architect to join our highly talented team in Canberra in taking Fujitsu to the next level of success. This is an opportunity to work across multiple service domains and interact with senior level management within Fujitsu and the customer environment.

You will have the primary responsibility as the solution owner and lead architect for large sales pursuits. You will also be covering the entire solution lifecycle allowing you to identify, design and deliver proposals for large and/or complex architectures and service delivery models. You will be a subject matter expert with experience in leading large design teams, proven experience working with and influencing at director level, achieving an understanding of customer business and commercial issues and the ability to demonstrate the benefits of a wide range of IT services to our clients.

Your previous experience in service design and solution construction within domains such as cloud services, hosted infrastructure, application services and end user computing will be highly regarded.

This is an exciting opportunity to join a high performing team whilst being generously rewarded for your achievements.

  • Working with customers to understand their business strategy and develop IT solutions and architecture.
  • Helping customers see how technological issues/solutions affect their business strategies.
  • Contributing to the definition of customers’ overall IT architecture.
  • Preparing world class bids for complex multi-party and international bids.
  • Managing the entire requirements process, including conformance assessment, for large bids or solutions.

  • Leading and coaching design teams, managing the work of specialists that are contributing to the design and implementation of the solution.

  • Establishing customer requirements for a solution
  • Building strong relationships and acting as a major influence in the customer choosing Fujitsu.

What You Need to Succeed?

  • Generalist knowledge of IT Services, in particular Managed Services solutions and infrastructure.
  • Experience in one or more of the following is preferable: SIAM, ServiceNow, Office365, AWS and Azure technologies.
  • Knowledge and experience developing solutions for Protected Cloud services (advantageous).
  • Exceptional proposal writing and presentation skills;
  • Business and commercial acumen;
  • ITIL experience;
  • Ability to present to technical and business audiences the benefits and features of Service and Technical solutions.


Why Fujitsu?
Working at Fujitsu, you will be joining a trusted public sector partner and the Number 1 non-Telco provider to Federal Government. At Fujitsu we believe one of our keys to success is identifying, supporting and growing our key talent in the business. With over 700 staff members across our Federal Government region, you will have the opportunity to work across some of Fujitsu's high profile Government projects.

You will have exposure to the latest technology, highly skilled people and access to a host of staff benefits including (depending on eligibility):

  • Gym memberships
